column2: What is the average number of number of movies added to the lists of user 8516503? Indicate how many movies did he/she give a rating score of 5.
column3:
SELECT 
  AVG(T1.list_movie_number) AS avg_movies, 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ratings T2 WHERE T2.user_id = 'user8516503' AND T2.rating_score = 5) AS count_rating_5
FROM 
  lists T1 
WHERE 
  T1.user_id = 'user8516503';
column4: SELECT AVG(T3.list_movie_number) , SUM(CASE WHEN T1.rating_score = 5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM ratings AS T1 INNER JOIN lists_users AS T2 ON T1.user_id = T2.user_id INNER JOIN lists AS T3 ON T2.user_id = T3.user_id WHERE T1.user_id = 8516503

column2: What is the full name of client whose email address is emily.garcia43@outlook.com?
column3:
SELECT CONCAT(first, ' ', middle, ' ', last) AS full_name 
FROM client 
WHERE email = 'emily.garcia43@outlook.com' 
LIMIT 1;
column4: SELECT first, middle, last FROM client WHERE email = 'emily.garcia43@outlook.com'

column2: In rated PG movies, how many of them released in June 1990?
column3:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM movie 
WHERE 'MPAA Rating' = 'PG' 
AND STRFTIME('%m', 'Release Date') = '06' 
AND STRFTIME('%Y', 'Release Date') = '1990';
column4: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM movie WHERE `MPAA Rating` = 'PG' AND `Release Date` LIKE '1990-06%'

column2: Which professor taught the most courses and what is the position of this person in the university?
column3:
SELECT T2.hasPosition, COUNT(T1.course_id) as num_courses 
FROM taughtBy T1 
JOIN person T2 ON T1.p_id = T2.p_id 
GROUP BY T2.p_id, T2.hasPosition 
ORDER BY num_courses DESC 
LIMIT 1;
column4: SELECT T1.p_id, T1.hasPosition FROM person AS T1 INNER JOIN taughtBy AS T2 ON T1.p_id = T2.p_id GROUP BY T1.p_id ORDER BY COUNT(T2.course_id) DESC LIMIT 1

column2: How many users installed the app but are not active?
column3:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT e.device_id) 
FROM events e 
JOIN app_events ae ON e.event_id = ae.event_id 
WHERE ae.is_installed = 1 AND ae.is_active = 0;
column4: SELECT COUNT(app_id) FROM app_events WHERE is_installed = 1 AND is_active = 0

column2: What was the total price of the products shipped to Rovelli Gifts Distributors Ltd. between 1/1/2003 and 12/31/2003?
column3:
SELECT SUM(od.quantityOrdered * od.priceEach) 
FROM customers c 
JOIN orders o ON c.customerNumber = o.customerNumber 
JOIN orderdetails od ON o.orderNumber = od.orderNumber 
WHERE c.customerName = 'Rovelli Gifts Distributors Ltd.' 
AND o.shippedDate BETWEEN '2003-01-01' AND '2003-12-31';
column4: SELECT T3.priceEach * T3.quantityOrdered FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customerNumber = T2.customerNumber INNER JOIN orderdetails AS T3 ON T2.orderNumber = T3.orderNumber WHERE T1.customerName = 'Rovelli Gifts' AND T2.status = 'Shipped' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.shippedDate) = '2003'

column2: What is the full address of the restaurant named "Sanuki Restaurant"?
column3:
SELECT 
 l.street_num, 
 l.street_name, 
 l.city, 
 g.region, 
 g.county 
FROM 
 location l 
JOIN 
 generalinfo gi ON l.id_restaurant = gi.id_restaurant 
JOIN 
 geographic g ON l.city = g.city 
WHERE 
 gi.label = 'Sanuki Restaurant';
column4: SELECT T2.city, T1.street_num, T1.street_name FROM location AS T1 INNER JOIN generalinfo AS T2 ON T1.id_restaurant = T2.id_restaurant WHERE T2.label = 'sanuki restaurant'

column2: How many unique directors with an average earnings of 2 and a quality of 3 have not made comedy films? List them.
column3:
SELECT directorid 
FROM directors 
WHERE avg_revenue = 2 AND d_quality = 3 
AND directorid NOT IN (
  SELECT directorid 
  FROM movies2directors 
  WHERE genre = 'Comedy'
)
column4: SELECT DISTINCT T1.directorid FROM directors AS T1 INNER JOIN movies2directors AS T2 ON T1.directorid = T2.directorid WHERE T1.d_quality = 3 AND T1.avg_revenue = 2 AND T2.genre != 'Comedy'

column2: Of all the nonessential genes that are not of the motorprotein class and whose phenotype is cell cycle defects, how many do not have a physical type of interaction?
column3:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT G.GeneID) 
FROM Genes G 
LEFT JOIN Interactions I ON G.GeneID = I.GeneID1 OR G.GeneID = I.GeneID2 
WHERE G.Essential = 'No' AND G.Class != 'motorprotein' AND G.Phenotype = 'cell cycle defects' AND I.Type != 'physical'
column4: SELECT COUNT(T1.GeneID) FROM Genes AS T1 INNER JOIN Interactions AS T2 ON T1.GeneID = T2.GeneID1 WHERE T2.Type != 'Physical' AND T1.Phenotype = 'Cell cycle defects' AND T1.Class != 'Motorproteins' AND T1.Essential = 'Non-Essential'

column2: How many negative comments are there in all the apps with 100,000,000+ installs?
column3:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM user_reviews 
JOIN playstore ON user_reviews.App = playstore.App 
WHERE playstore.Installs >= '100,000,000' AND user_reviews.Sentiment = 'Negative';
column4: SELECT COUNT(T2.Sentiment) FROM playstore AS T1 INNER JOIN user_reviews AS T2 ON T1.App = T2.App WHERE T1.Installs = '100,000,000+' AND T2.Sentiment = 'Negative'

column2: Name the sales team and the region of order number 'SO - 000137'.
column3:
SELECT T2.'Sales Team', T2.Region 
FROM 'Sales Orders' T1 
JOIN 'Sales Team' T2 ON T1._SalesTeamID = T2.SalesTeamID 
WHERE T1.OrderNumber = 'SO -000137';
column4: SELECT T2.`Sales Team`, T2.Region FROM `Sales Orders` AS T1 INNER JOIN `Sales Team` AS T2 ON T2.SalesTeamID = T1._SalesTeamID WHERE T1.OrderNumber = 'SO - 000137'

column2: What percentage of donations are given via a giving or campaign page? List the primary area of those donations.
column3:
SELECT 
  p.primary_focus_area, 
  COUNT(d.donationid) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM donations WHERE via_giving_page = 1) AS percentage
FROM 
  donations d
JOIN 
  projects p ON d.projectid = p.projectid
WHERE 
  d.via_giving_page = 1
GROUP BY 
  p.primary_focus_area
column4: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.via_giving_page = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(donation_total), ( SELECT T2.primary_focus_area FROM donations AS T1 INNER JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.projectid = T2.projectid WHERE T1.via_giving_page = 't' GROUP BY T2.primary_focus_area ORDER BY SUM(T1.donation_total) DESC LIMIT 1 ) result FROM donations AS T1 INNER JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.projectid = T2.projectid

column2: How many games were sold on PS3 platform in Japan?
column3:
SELECT SUM(rs.num_sales) 
FROM region_sales rs 
JOIN region r ON rs.region_id = r.id 
JOIN game_platform gp ON rs.game_platform_id = gp.id 
JOIN platform p ON gp.platform_id = p.id 
WHERE r.region_name = 'Japan' AND p.platform_name = 'PS3';
column4: SELECT SUM(T1.num_sales * 100000) FROM region_sales AS T1 INNER JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id = T2.id INNER JOIN game_platform AS T3 ON T1.game_platform_id = T3.id INNER JOIN platform AS T4 ON T3.platform_id = T4.id WHERE T2.region_name = 'Japan' AND T4.platform_name = 'PS3'

column2: Write down the summary of episode whereby it has crew members that are not included in the credit list.
column3:
SELECT DISTINCT E.summary 
FROM Episode E 
JOIN Credit C ON E.episode_id = C.episode_id 
WHERE C.credited = 'false';
column4: SELECT T1.summary FROM Episode AS T1 INNER JOIN Credit AS T2 ON T1.episode_id = T2.episode_id WHERE T2.credited = 'false';

column2: Please check if student 124 is disabled male.
column3:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM person 
JOIN male ON person.name = male.name 
JOIN disabled ON person.name = disabled.name 
WHERE person.name = 'student124';
column4: SELECT IIF(T2.name IS NULL, 'female', 'male') FROM male AS T1 LEFT JOIN disabled AS T2 ON T1.name = T2.name WHERE T1.name = 'student124'

column2: Which brand in 2012 has the lowest star rating and contains cane sugar as well as honey?
column3:
SELECT T1.BrandName 
FROM rootbeerbrand T1 
JOIN rootbeerreview T2 ON T1.BrandID = T2.BrandID 
WHERE T1.CaneSugar = 'True' AND T1.Honey = 'True' 
AND T2.ReviewDate LIKE '2012%' 
ORDER BY T2.StarRating ASC 
LIMIT 1;
column4: SELECT DISTINCT T1.BrandName FROM rootbeerbrand AS T1 INNER JOIN rootbeerreview AS T2 ON T1.BrandID = T2.BrandID WHERE T1.CaneSugar = 'TRUE' AND T1.Honey = 'TRUE' AND T2.StarRating = 1 AND T2.ReviewDate LIKE '2012%'

column2: Please list the names of all the dishes that appeared on the menu "Zentral Theater Terrace".
column3:
SELECT DISTINCT D.name 
FROM Dish D 
JOIN MenuItem MI ON D.id = MI.dish_id 
JOIN MenuPage MP ON MI.menu_page_id = MP.id 
JOIN Menu M ON MP.menu_id = M.id 
WHERE M.name = 'Zentral Theater Terrace';
column4: SELECT T4.name FROM MenuItem AS T1 INNER JOIN MenuPage AS T2 ON T1.menu_page_id = T2.id INNER JOIN Menu AS T3 ON T2.menu_id = T3.id INNER JOIN Dish AS T4 ON T1.dish_id = T4.id WHERE T3.name = 'Zentral Theater Terrace'

column2: How many times does the Catalan word "nombre" repeat itself?
column3:
SELECT T1.occurrences 
FROM words AS T1 
INNER JOIN langs_words AS T2 ON T1.wid = T2.wid 
INNER JOIN langs AS T3 ON T2.lid = T3.lid 
WHERE T1.word = 'nombre' AND T3.lang = 'Catalan';
column4: SELECT T1.occurrences FROM langs_words AS T1 INNER JOIN words AS T2 ON T1.wid = T2.wid WHERE T2.word = 'nombre'

column2: Had Bitcoin's price increased or decreased on 2013/5/5 compared with the price 7 days before?
column3:
SELECT 
 h1.price AS price_on_date, 
 h2.price AS price_7_days_before, 
 CASE 
 WHEN h1.price > h2.price THEN 'increased'
 WHEN h1.price < h2.price THEN 'decreased'
 ELSE 'unchanged'
 END AS change_status
FROM 
 historical h1
JOIN 
 historical h2 ON h1.coin_id = h2.coin_id
JOIN 
 coins c ON h1.coin_id = c.id
WHERE 
 c.name = 'Bitcoin' 
 AND h1.date = '2013-05-05' 
 AND h2.date = (SELECT MAX(date) FROM historical WHERE date <= DATE('2013-05-05', '-7 day') AND coin_id = h1.coin_id)
LIMIT 1;

column2: Among the coaches who was never a player, who has highest percentage of game winning? Provide the given name of the coach and team he coached.

column2: Among the days on which over 100 units of item no.5 were sold in store no.3, on which date was the temperature range the biggest?
column3:
SELECT w.date 
FROM sales_in_weather s 
JOIN weather w ON s.date = w.date 
JOIN relation r ON s.store_nbr = r.store_nbr AND w.station_nbr = r.station_nbr 
WHERE s.store_nbr = 3 AND s.item_nbr = 5 AND s.units > 100 
ORDER BY (w.tmax - w.tmin) DESC 
LIMIT 1;
column4: SELECT T2.`date` FROM relation AS T1 INNER JOIN sales_in_weather AS T2 ON T1.store_nbr = T2.store_nbr INNER JOIN weather AS T3 ON T1.station_nbr = T3.station_nbr WHERE T2.store_nbr = 3 AND T2.item_nbr = 5 AND T2.units > 100 ORDER BY tmax - tmin DESC LIMIT 1

column4: SELECT T2.City, T1.Capital FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN located AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.Country INNER JOIN river AS T3 ON T3.Name = T2.River WHERE T3.Name = 'Euphrat'

column2: Calculate the average level difference between the Marketing editors hired by the US and non-US publishers?
column3:
SELECT AVG(j1.min_lvl - j2.min_lvl) 
FROM jobs j1 
JOIN employee e1 ON j1.min_lvl = e1.job_id 
JOIN publishers p1 ON e1.pub_id = p1.pub_id 
JOIN jobs j2 ON j2.job_desc = 'Marketing Manager' 
JOIN employee e2 ON j2.min_lvl = e2.job_id 
JOIN publishers p2 ON e2.pub_id = p2.pub_id 
WHERE p1.country = 'USA' AND p2.country != 'USA'
column4: SELECT (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country = 'USA' THEN job_lvl ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country = 'USA' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) - (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country != 'USA' THEN job_lvl ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country != 'USA' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) FROM publishers AS T1 INNER JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.pub_id = T2.pub_id INNER JOIN jobs AS T3 ON T2.job_id = T3.job_id WHERE T3.job_desc = 'Managing Editor'
column6: [{"(CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country = 'USA' THEN job_lvl ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) \/ SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country = 'USA' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) - (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country != 'USA' THEN job_lvl ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) \/ SUM(CASE WHEN T1.country != 'USA' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))":32.0}]

column2: Calculate the difference in the average age of elderly and middle-aged clients in the Northeast region.
column3:
SELECT 
  AVG(CASE WHEN c.age >= 65 THEN c.age END) - AVG(CASE WHEN c.age BETWEEN 40 AND 64 THEN c.age END) AS avg_age_diff
FROM 
  client c
JOIN 
  state s ON c.state = s.State
WHERE 
  s.Region = 'Northeast' AND (c.age >= 65 OR (c.age BETWEEN 40 AND 64));
column4: SELECT (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.age BETWEEN 35 AND 55 THEN T1.age ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T1.age BETWEEN 35 AND 55 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) - (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.age > 65 THEN T1.age ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T1.age > 65 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS difference FROM client AS T1 INNER JOIN district AS T2 ON T1.district_id = T2.district_id INNER JOIN state AS T3 ON T2.state_abbrev = T3.StateCode WHERE T3.Region = 'Northeast'

  ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC 
  LIMIT 1
)

column2: How many games in the database belong to the genre of sports?
column3:
SELECT COUNT(g.id) 
FROM game g 
JOIN genre ge ON g.genre_id = ge.id 
WHERE ge.genre_name = 'sports';
column4: SELECT COUNT(T1.id) FROM game AS T1 INNER JOIN genre AS T2 ON T1.genre_id = T2.id WHERE T2.genre_name = 'Sports'

column2: Who are the authors of the paper "Determination of Planetary Meteorology from Aerobot Flight Sensors"?
column3:
SELECT T2.Name 
FROM Paper AS T1 
INNER JOIN PaperAuthor AS T2 
ON T1.Id = T2.PaperId 
WHERE T1.Title = 'Determination of Planetary Meteorology from Aerobot Flight Sensors';
column4: SELECT T2.Name FROM Paper AS T1 INNER JOIN PaperAuthor AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.PaperId WHERE T1.Title = 'Determination of Planetary Meteorology FROM Aerobot Flight Sensors'
